want to find something

00:35:31.220 --> 00:35:34.070
that you are passionate
about because that's

00:35:34.070 --> 00:35:35.220
going to keep you going.

00:35:35.220 --> 00:35:39.740
And a lot of the issues and
the challenges that face us

00:35:39.740 --> 00:35:41.180
are not easy to solve.

00:35:41.180 --> 00:35:43.670
So you want to have
that tenaciousness,

00:35:43.670 --> 00:35:48.320
and stick-to-itiveness to
really stay with an organization

00:35:48.320 --> 00:35:50.910
and take that long-term view.

00:35:50.910 --> 00:35:54.050
So once you identify
what the passion is,

00:35:54.050 --> 00:35:55.685
it's just researching
the options.

00:35:55.685 --> 00:36:01.280
There's a lot of groups involved
in ocean conservation, land

00:36:01.280 --> 00:36:04.760
preservation,
education, whatever

00:36:04.760 --> 00:36:08.940
it is, hunger, immigration
issues, voter rights.

00:36:08.940 --> 00:36:10.410
I mean, there are so many.

00:36:10.410 --> 00:36:14.240
And to just do your homework and
find out who the leadership is.

00:36:14.240 --> 00:36:17.060
I really believe that
finding those leaders that

00:36:17.060 --> 00:36:22.910
are really at the forefront of
being efficient, and effective,

00:36:22.910 --> 00:36:25.670
and charismatic are the
ones, at least for me,

00:36:25.670 --> 00:36:28.890
that I get attracted to.

00:36:28.890 --> 00:36:31.970
But I would say the
passion, the research,

00:36:31.970 --> 00:36:35.540
and then engage in whatever
way, whether it's your time,

00:36:35.540 --> 00:36:39.350
volunteering, donating.

00:36:39.350 --> 00:36:41.150
Obviously, many of
these organizations

00:36:41.150 --> 00:36:47.180
